{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Cap \u2018pay later\u2019 parking and toll penalties, and require a pay-on-exit option",
        "additional_details": "Many tolls and car parks now require drivers to remember to pay later online. If they forget, they can receive mammoth penalties for an original charge of only a few pounds. We believe this punishes forgetfulness, not dishonesty, and disproportionately affects busy people, carers, parents and those with attention or memory difficulties. Operators should be required to provide pay-on-exit options and to limit penalties to reasonable administrative costs so genuine mistakes are not treated like deliberate non-payment.",
        "background": "Introduce legislation to cap penalties for \u201cpay later\u201d tolls and car parks and require operators to provide a clear pay-on-exit option. Where drivers forget to pay, additional reminder/collection charges must be capped at a small administrative fee (for example \u00a35) before a larger penalty.",
